V{{Infobox philosopher\u000a|region = [[Western Philosophy]]\u000a|era    = [[21st-century philosophy]]\u000a|image = \u000a|name  = Ernest Sosa\u000a|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1940|6|17}}\u000a|birth_place = [[Cárdenas, Cuba]]\u000a|alma_mater       = [[University of Miami]]<br>[[University of Pittsburgh]]\u000a|institutions     = [[Brown University]]<br>[[Rutgers University]]\u000a|school_tradition = [[Analytic philosophy|Analytic]]\u000a|main_interests   = [[Metaphysics]]{{·}}[[Epistemology]]{{·}}[[Philosophy of mind]]\u000a|notable_ideas    = [[Virtue epistemology]]\u000a|influences = \u000a|influenced = \u000a}}\u000a{{Infobox scientist\u000a| name              = Ernest Sosa\u000a| thesis_title      = Directives: A Logico-Philosophical Inquiry\u000a| thesis_url        = \u000a| thesis_year       = 1964\u000a| doctoral_advisor  = [[Nicholas Rescher]]\u000a| doctoral_students = [[Brie Gertler]]<br>[[John Greco (philosopher)|John Greco]]\u000a}}\u000a'''Ernest Sosa''' (born June 17, 1940) is an American philosopher primarily interested in [[epistemology]].<ref>{{cite LAF|id=n 79055185}}</ref> He is Board of Governors [[Professor]] of [[Philosophy]] at [[Rutgers University]] since 2007, but spent most of his career at [[Brown University]].  \u000a\u000a== Education and career ==\u000a\u000aBorn in [[Cárdenas, Cuba]] on June 17, 1940,<ref>The dictionary of modern American philosophers, Volume 1 by Richard T. Hull, Continuum International Publishing Group, 2005, p.2287.</ref> Sosa earned his BA and MA from the [[University of Miami]] and his PhD from the [[University of Pittsburgh]] in 1964 where his dissertation was supervised by [[Nicholas Rescher]].\u000a\u000aHe has been at Rutgers full-time since January 2007; he had been at [[Brown University]] since 1964.  While full-time at Brown, he was also a distinguished visiting professor at Rutgers every spring from 1998-2006.<ref name=CV>{{cite web|url=http://web.mac.com/ernestsosa/Site/CV.html|title=Ernest Sosa - Abbreviated Curriculum Vitae|author=Ernest Sosa|accessdate=July 23, 2011}}</ref>  Sosa has been described as "one of the most important epistemologists of the last half-century."<ref>https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/23005-ernest-sosa-and-his-critics/</ref>\u000a\u000aSosa is a past president of the [[American Philosophical Association]] and a Fellow of the [[American Academy of Arts & Sciences]].<ref name=CV />  He edits the philosophical journals ''[[Noûs]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wiley.com/bw/editors.asp?ref=0029-4624&site=1|title=Noûs - Journal Information|publisher=Wiley Blackwell|year=2010|accessdate= July 23, 2011}}</ref> and ''[[Philosophy and Phenomenological Research]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wiley.com/bw/editors.asp?ref=0031-8205&site=1|title=Philosophy and Phenomenological Research - Journal Information|publisher=Wiley Blackwell|year=2011|accessdate=July 23, 2011}}</ref> In 2005, he delivered the [[John Locke Lectures]] at Oxford,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk/lectures/john_locke_lectures/past_lectures|title=Past Lectures - Faculty of Philosophy|accessdate=July 23, 2011}}</ref> which formed the basis of his 2007 book.\u000a\u000aHe was also the 2010 recipient of the [[Nicholas Rescher]] Prize for contributions to systematic philosophy, conferred by the [[University of Pittsburgh]] biennially.<ref>http://www.news.pitt.edu/news/philosopher-ernest-sosa-inaugural-recipient-pitt%E2%80%99s-prestigious-rescher-prize</ref>\u000a\u000aHis son, [[David Sosa]], is a professor and chair of the philosophy department at the [[University of Texas, Austin]].\u000a\u000a== Philosophy ==\u000a\u000aIn addition to epistemology, Sosa has also written on [[metaphysics]], [[modern philosophy]] and [[philosophy of mind]].  In his books ''Knowledge in Perspective'' (1991) and ''A Virtue Epistemology'' (2007), Sosa defends a form of [[virtue epistemology]] called "virtue perspectivism", which distinguishes animal knowledge from reflective knowledge.\u000a\u000a==Bibliography==\u000a*''Knowledge in Perspective'' (Cambridge University Press, 1991)\u000a*''Epistemic Justification'' (Blackwell Publishers, 2003), with L. BonJour\u000a*''Ernest Sosa and his Critics'', ed by J. Greco (Blackwell, 2004)\u000a*''A Virtue Epistemology'' (Oxford University Press, 2007)\u000a*''Reflective Knowledge'' (Oxford University Press, 2009)\u000a*''Knowing Full Well'' (Princeton University Press, 2011)\u000a*''Virtuous Thoughts: The Philosophy of Ernest Sosa'', ed by J. Turri (Springer 2013)\u000a\u000a==See also==\u000a*[[American philosophy]]\u000a*[[List of American philosophers]]\u000a\u000a== References ==\u000a<references/>\u000a\u000a== External links ==\u000a*[http://www.ernestsosa.com Ernest Sosa's home page]\u000a\u000a{{Authority control}}\u000a\u000a{{DEFAULTSORT:Sosa, Ernest}}\u000a[[Category:Living people]]\u000a[[Category:Rutgers University faculty]]\u000a[[Category:University of Miami alumni]]\u000a[[Category:University of Pittsburgh alumni]]\u000a[[Category:Brown University faculty]]\u000a[[Category:American philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:Analytic philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:Epistemologists]]\u000a[[Category:1940 births]]\u000a[[Category:Fellows of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\u000a\u000a{{US-philosopher-stub}}
